257
00:15:58,640 --> 00:15:59,640
We take this one down,

258
00:15:59,720 --> 00:16:02,560
the Justice Department
will give us the rest of the year off.

259
00:16:02,640 --> 00:16:04,920
-Are you sure?
-There's no question.

260
00:16:06,720 --> 00:16:07,760
It's her.

261
00:16:08,800 --> 00:16:10,240
How bad is it, Rory? What can we do?

262
00:16:10,320 --> 00:16:13,160
Just keep her conscious.
Stay with us, Mels!

263
00:16:13,640 --> 00:16:15,880
Hey, look at me. Just hold on.

264
00:16:17,360 --> 00:16:18,840
I used to

265
00:16:18,920 --> 00:16:22,040
dream about you.
All those stories Amy used to tell me.

266
00:16:22,120 --> 00:16:25,200
What stories? Tell me what stories?
Vampires in Venice?

267
00:16:25,480 --> 00:16:28,000
When I was little,

268
00:16:28,800 --> 00:16:29,800
I was going to marry you.

269
00:16:29,880 --> 00:16:32,760
Good idea, let's get married.
You stay alive and I'll marry you. Deal?

270
00:16:34,360 --> 00:16:36,240
Shouldn't you ask
my parents' permission?

271
00:16:36,320 --> 00:16:38,480
As soon as you're well,
I'll get them on the phone.

272
00:16:38,560 --> 00:16:40,520
Might as well do it now.

273
00:16:40,640 --> 00:16:42,360
Since they're both right here.

274
00:16:50,040 --> 00:16:51,560
Penny in the air.

275
00:16:57,720 --> 00:16:59,120
Penny drops.

276
00:17:02,360 --> 00:17:03,680
What the hell is going on?

277
00:17:03,760 --> 00:17:05,680
Back, back, back. Get back!

278
00:17:07,000 --> 00:17:09,160
Last time I did this, I...

279
00:17:09,240 --> 00:17:11,240
I ended up a toddler.

280
00:17:11,600 --> 00:17:13,440
In the middle of New York.

281
00:17:13,520 --> 00:17:15,640
Okay, Doctor,
explain what is happening, please.

282
00:17:15,720 --> 00:17:18,160
Mels, short for...

283
00:17:18,360 --> 00:17:19,480
Melody.

284
00:17:19,680 --> 00:17:21,560
Yeah, I named my daughter after her.

285
00:17:21,920 --> 00:17:23,240
You named your daughter

286
00:17:24,200 --> 00:17:26,440
after your daughter.

287
00:17:26,520 --> 00:17:28,520
It took me years to find you two.

288
00:17:28,600 --> 00:17:30,800
I'm so glad I did.

289
00:17:30,880 --> 00:17:34,960
And you see?
It all worked out in the end, didn't it?

290
00:17:36,240 --> 00:17:38,160
You got to raise me after all.

291
00:17:38,240 --> 00:17:39,680
You're Melody?

292
00:17:39,880 --> 00:17:42,960
-But, if she's Melody, that means...
-Shut up, Dad.

293
00:17:43,360 --> 00:17:45,920
I'm focusing on a dress size.

294
00:17:46,080 --> 00:17:48,360
(MELS SCREAMING)

295
00:18:02,120 --> 00:18:05,320
(EXCLAIMS)

296
00:18:08,080 --> 00:18:10,760
Right. Let's see, then.

297
00:18:11,840 --> 00:18:14,800
Ooh, it's all going on down there,
isn't it?

298
00:18:15,920 --> 00:18:16,920
The hair!

299
00:18:17,000 --> 00:18:18,840
(GASPING) The hair!

300
00:18:18,920 --> 00:18:21,080
It just doesn't stop, does it?

301
00:18:21,160 --> 00:18:22,600
Look at that.

302
00:18:22,920 --> 00:18:25,040
Everything changes.

303
00:18:25,640 --> 00:18:28,160
Oh, but I love it. I love it!

304
00:18:28,440 --> 00:18:31,640
I'm all sort of...mature.

305
00:18:33,280 --> 00:18:35,400
Hello, Benjamin.

306
00:18:36,920 --> 00:18:38,080
(WHISPERS) Who's Benjamin?

307
00:18:38,600 --> 00:18:39,600
The teeth.

308
00:18:39,680 --> 00:18:41,480
(GASPING) The teeth.

309
00:18:41,680 --> 00:18:44,400
The teeth. Oh, look at them!

310
00:18:45,280 --> 00:18:47,560
Watch out, that bow tie.

311
00:18:48,560 --> 00:18:51,400
Excuse me, you lot.
I need to weigh myself.

312
00:18:59,680 --> 00:19:01,720
That's Melody.

313
00:19:02,440 --> 00:19:04,080
It's River Song.

314
00:19:04,840 --> 00:19:05,840
Who's River Song?

315
00:19:08,400 --> 00:19:09,400
Spoilers.

316
00:19:09,800 --> 00:19:11,960
Spoilers? What spoilers?

317
00:19:13,080 --> 00:19:15,000
Hang on, just something I have to check.

318
00:19:18,280 --> 00:19:20,280
Does anybody else find this day
just a bit difficult?

319
00:19:21,480 --> 00:19:23,040
I'm getting this sort of banging
in my head.

320
00:19:23,120 --> 00:19:24,840
Yeah, I think that's Hitler
in the cupboard.

321
00:19:24,920 --> 00:19:26,320
That's not helping.

322
00:19:26,400 --> 00:19:28,440
This isn't the River Song we know yet.

323
00:19:28,520 --> 00:19:30,760
This is her right at the start.

324
00:19:30,840 --> 00:19:32,160
Doesn't even know her name.

325
00:19:32,240 --> 00:19:34,800
RIVER: Oh! That's magnificent!

326
00:19:39,080 --> 00:19:41,200
I'm going to wear lots of jodhpurs.

327
00:19:43,120 --> 00:19:45,280
Well, that's her, all right.

328
00:19:45,880 --> 00:19:47,280
Melody Pond.

329
00:19:48,480 --> 00:19:50,440
The woman who kills the Doctor.

330
00:19:50,920 --> 00:19:53,160
Well, now, enough of all that.

331
00:19:53,240 --> 00:19:55,280
-Down to business.
-Oh! Hello.

332
00:19:55,600 --> 00:19:56,760
I thought we were getting married?

333
00:19:57,960 --> 00:20:00,720
I told you. I'm not a wedding person.

334
00:20:00,800 --> 00:20:01,800
Doctor, what's she doing?

335
00:20:01,880 --> 00:20:03,760
-What she's programmed to.
-And where'd she get the gun?

336
00:20:03,840 --> 00:20:05,800
Hello, Benjamin.

337
00:20:06,640 --> 00:20:07,720
Hello, Benjamin.

338
00:20:10,720 --> 00:20:11,720
You noticed.

339
00:20:11,880 --> 00:20:13,320
(GUN CLICKS)

340
00:20:14,160 --> 00:20:15,160
Of course I noticed.

341
00:20:15,400 --> 00:20:16,840
(SCREAMING)

342
00:20:21,440 --> 00:20:22,480
(CLICKS)

343
00:20:22,640 --> 00:20:25,320
As soon as I knew you were coming,
I tidied up a bit.

344
00:20:26,720 --> 00:20:27,720
I know you did.

345
00:20:28,560 --> 00:20:30,160
Watch out, that bow tie.

346
00:20:33,080 --> 00:20:34,080
I know you know.

347
00:20:39,920 --> 00:20:42,160
Goodness, is killing you
going to take all day?

348
00:20:42,240 --> 00:20:43,720
Why? You busy?

349
00:20:43,800 --> 00:20:46,000
Oh, I'm not complaining.

350
00:20:48,360 --> 00:20:51,000
If you were in a hurry, you could have
killed me in the cornfield.

351
00:20:51,080 --> 00:20:52,320
We'd only just met.

352
00:20:52,400 --> 00:20:54,920
I'm a psychopath, I'm not rude.

353
00:20:55,560 --> 00:20:57,800
(GUN CLICKING, AMY SCREAMS)

354
00:21:01,160 --> 00:21:03,360
You are not a psychopath.

355
00:21:04,240 --> 00:21:06,320
Why would she be a psychopath?

356
00:21:06,840 --> 00:21:09,440
Oh, Mummy, Mummy, pay attention.

357
00:21:10,200 --> 00:21:13,000
I was trained and conditioned
for one purpose.

358
00:21:13,520 --> 00:21:16,440
-I was born to kill the Doctor.
-Demon's Run.

359
00:21:16,520 --> 00:21:19,320
Remember?
This is what they were building.

360
00:21:19,760 --> 00:21:21,920
My bespoke psychopath.

361
00:21:22,040 --> 00:21:24,880
-I'm all yours, sweetie.
-Only River Song gets to call me that.

362
00:21:24,960 --> 00:21:26,920
-And who's River Song?
-An old friend of mine.

363
00:21:27,000 --> 00:21:28,000
Stupid name.

364
00:21:28,880 --> 00:21:31,160
(GASPING) Look at that!

365
00:21:33,120 --> 00:21:35,400
Berlin on the eve of war.

366
00:21:35,560 --> 00:21:38,640
A whole world
about to tear itself apart.

367
00:21:41,680 --> 00:21:43,320
Now, that's my kind of town.

368
00:21:44,160 --> 00:21:47,440
Mum, Dad, don't follow me.
And yes, that is a warning.

369
00:21:48,040 --> 00:21:50,360
No warning for me, then?

370
00:21:50,440 --> 00:21:51,960
No need, my love.

371
00:21:52,040 --> 00:21:54,520
The deed is done. And so are you.

372
00:21:55,600 --> 00:21:57,080
Doctor, what's wrong?

373
00:21:57,360 --> 00:21:59,400
What have you done?

374
00:21:59,520 --> 00:22:00,520
River!

375
00:22:00,600 --> 00:22:04,600
Oh, River, River, River.
More than a friend, I think.

376
00:22:04,720 --> 00:22:05,840
What have you done?

377
00:22:07,120 --> 00:22:09,600
It was never going to be a gun for you,
Doctor,

378
00:22:10,640 --> 00:22:11,800
the man of peace,

379
00:22:12,440 --> 00:22:15,520
who understands every kind
of warfare except,

380
00:22:15,920 --> 00:22:17,920
perhaps, the cruellest.

381
00:22:20,800 --> 00:22:22,080
I'm all yours, sweetie.

382
00:22:23,840 --> 00:22:24,840
Kiss, kiss.

383
00:22:28,600 --> 00:22:30,040
What's wrong with you?
What's she done to you?

384
00:22:30,120 --> 00:22:31,800
Poisoned me, but I'm fine.

385
00:22:32,080 --> 00:22:34,360
Well, no. I'm dying.

386
00:22:34,520 --> 00:22:36,240
-But I've got a plan.
-What plan?

387
00:22:37,080 --> 00:22:39,040
Not dying, see? Fine.

388
00:22:40,160 --> 00:22:41,160
Scanning him.

389
00:22:42,400 --> 00:22:44,440
-He's dying, all right.
-But he can't be.

390
00:22:44,600 --> 00:22:46,360
(GROANING IN PAIN)

391
00:22:47,000 --> 00:22:48,520
Okay, what do we do? How do we help you?

392
00:22:48,680 --> 00:22:50,400
Take this. The Tardis can override it.

393
00:22:50,760 --> 00:22:52,320
Now, go, get after her.

394
00:22:57,400 --> 00:22:59,680
(MEN SHOUTING)

395
00:23:03,520 --> 00:23:04,880
Hello, boys.

396
00:23:06,560 --> 00:23:07,560
You said the smoke was deadly.

397
00:23:07,640 --> 00:23:09,960
No, the smoke's fine,
the poison will kill me first.

398
00:23:10,040 --> 00:23:11,880
-Now, get after River...
-I don't understand, okay?

399
00:23:11,960 --> 00:23:13,720
One minute she's going to marry you,
and then she's going to kill you.

400
00:23:13,800 --> 00:23:16,040
Ah, well, she's been brainwashed,
it all makes sense.

401
00:23:16,120 --> 00:23:18,080
Plus, she's a woman.

402
00:23:18,400 --> 00:23:20,320
Oh, shut up, I'm dying.

403
00:23:22,960 --> 00:23:24,760
Extractor fans on!

404
00:23:25,520 --> 00:23:27,120
Oh! That worked.

405
00:23:27,640 --> 00:23:28,880
What are you doing here?

406
00:23:29,000 --> 00:23:32,440
Well, I was on my way to this gay gypsy
Bar Mitzvah for the disabled,

407
00:23:32,520 --> 00:23:35,280
when I suddenly thought,
"Gosh, the Third Reich's a bit rubbish.

408
00:23:35,360 --> 00:23:36,920
"I think I'lLL kill the Fuhrer.”

409
00:23:37,440 --> 00:23:38,440
Who's with me?

410
00:23:40,120 --> 00:23:41,320
Shoot her.

411
00:23:42,000 --> 00:23:43,800
-No!
-(MACHINE GUNS FIRING)

412
00:23:47,080 --> 00:23:48,080
Tip for you all,

413
00:23:49,200 --> 00:23:51,600
never shoot a girl
while she's regenerating.

414
00:23:53,560 --> 00:23:55,320
(RIVER LAUGHING)

415
00:23:57,400 --> 00:23:58,400
Ah!

416
00:23:59,920 --> 00:24:02,080
RIVER: Now, that hit the spot.

417
00:24:04,440 --> 00:24:06,520
Thanks, boys. Ha! Call me.

418
00:24:06,600 --> 00:24:07,760
What are you doing?

419
00:24:07,840 --> 00:24:11,400
New body, new town...
I'm going shopping.

420
00:24:19,640 --> 00:24:22,320
Look, I know how this looks.

421
00:24:23,000 --> 00:24:24,520
Let me explain everything
from the beginning.

422
00:24:27,200 --> 00:24:29,080
-Heil!
-Heil!

423
00:24:31,000 --> 00:24:32,280
Come on!

424
00:24:34,920 --> 00:24:36,320
Can you ride a motorbike?

425
00:24:36,400 --> 00:24:38,840
I expect so. It's that sort of day.

426
00:24:44,600 --> 00:24:48,760
Okay. This time, let's do the bike, too.

427
00:24:53,200 --> 00:24:54,520
You see? He can't be dying.

428
00:24:54,600 --> 00:24:57,120
But the Doctor is confirmed deceased.
We have his record.

429
00:24:57,200 --> 00:24:58,360
But he doesn't die here.

430
00:24:58,440 --> 00:25:01,800
He does in Utah, by Lake Silencio,
April 22nd, 2011.

431
00:25:01,880 --> 00:25:03,920
Time can be rewritten. Remember Kennedy?

432
00:25:04,000 --> 00:25:06,240
This time can't.
It's a confirmed, fixed point.

433
00:25:06,320 --> 00:25:09,800
The Doctor must always die exactly then.
He always has. And he always will.

434
00:25:09,880 --> 00:25:12,400
Then someone screwed up,
because he's dying right now.

435
00:25:14,000 --> 00:25:16,240
Shut it down. I need an interface.

436
00:25:16,480 --> 00:25:18,400
Voice interface, come on, emergency.

437
00:25:20,840 --> 00:25:22,600
Voice interface enabled.

438
00:25:22,680 --> 00:25:25,200
No, no, no! Give me someone I like!

439
00:25:27,040 --> 00:25:30,640
Oh! Thanks! Give me guilt.

440
00:25:33,240 --> 00:25:34,400
Also guilt.

441
00:25:36,880 --> 00:25:38,880
More quilt. Ahh...

442
00:25:39,720 --> 00:25:44,360
Come on! There must be someone left in
the universe I haven't screwed up yet.

443
00:25:44,880 --> 00:25:48,480
-Ah.
-AMELIA: Voice interface enabled.

444
00:25:52,640 --> 00:25:53,680
Oh.

445
00:25:54,000 --> 00:25:55,400
Amelia Pond!

446
00:25:56,280 --> 00:25:58,200
Before I got it all wrong.

447
00:25:58,440 --> 00:26:00,000
My sweet little Amelia.

448
00:26:00,720 --> 00:26:03,840
I am not Amelia Pond.
I am a voice interface.

449
00:26:03,920 --> 00:26:06,640
Hey, let's run away and have adventures.
Come along, Pond.

450
00:26:06,720 --> 00:26:09,760
I am not Amelia Pond.
I am a voice interface.

451
00:26:10,000 --> 00:26:12,800
You are so Scottish. How am I doing?

452
00:26:12,920 --> 00:26:16,760
Your system has been contaminated
by the poison of the Judas Tree.

453
00:26:16,880 --> 00:26:18,760
You will be dead in 32 minutes.

454
00:26:19,000 --> 00:26:22,280
Okay, so, basically better regenerate.
That's what you're saying?

455
00:26:22,520 --> 00:26:24,120
Regeneration disabled.

456
00:26:24,240 --> 00:26:26,080
You will be dead in 32 minutes.

457
00:26:26,160 --> 00:26:27,640
Unless I'm cured, yeah?

458
00:26:27,720 --> 00:26:30,560
There is no cure.
You will be dead in 32 minutes.

459
00:26:30,640 --> 00:26:32,560
Why do you keep saying that?

460
00:26:32,640 --> 00:26:34,800
Because you will be dead in 32 minutes.

461
00:26:34,880 --> 00:26:36,080
You see? There you go again.

462
00:26:36,160 --> 00:26:40,520
Basically skipping 31 whole minutes
when I'm absolutely fine.

463
00:26:40,640 --> 00:26:42,000
It's Scottish, that's all I'm saying.

464
00:26:42,080 --> 00:26:44,280
You will be fine for 31 minutes.

465
00:26:44,360 --> 00:26:45,840
You will be dead in 32 minutes.

466
00:26:45,920 --> 00:26:47,680
Scotland's never conquered anywhere,
you know.

467
00:26:47,920 --> 00:26:49,280
Not even a Shetland.

468
00:26:49,720 --> 00:26:51,080
River needs me.

469
00:26:51,160 --> 00:26:52,840
She's only just beginning,
I can't die now.

470
00:26:52,920 --> 00:26:56,080
You will not die now.
You will die in 32 minutes.

471
00:26:56,160 --> 00:26:59,000
I'm going out in the first round.
Ringing any bells?

472
00:26:59,080 --> 00:27:00,720
Ahh!

473
00:27:04,760 --> 00:27:07,080
Need something for the pain now.

474
00:27:07,320 --> 00:27:08,400
Come on, Amelia.

475
00:27:09,120 --> 00:27:10,440
It's me.

476
00:27:11,040 --> 00:27:12,240
Please.

477
00:27:12,440 --> 00:27:15,080
I am not Amelia Pond.
I am a voice interface.

478
00:27:15,640 --> 00:27:17,720
Amelia, listen to me.

479
00:27:19,880 --> 00:27:21,920
I can be brave for you.

480
00:27:22,120 --> 00:27:24,240
But you have got to tell me how.

481
00:27:24,360 --> 00:27:27,320
I am not Amelia Pond.
I am a voice interface.

482
00:27:27,520 --> 00:27:28,760
(SOFTLY) Amelia...

483
00:27:29,480 --> 00:27:30,840
Please...

484
00:27:31,280 --> 00:27:32,320
Please...

485
00:27:34,840 --> 00:27:36,640
Fish fingers and custard.

486
00:27:39,040 --> 00:27:40,680
What did you say?

487
00:27:47,120 --> 00:27:49,040
Fish fingers and custard?

488
00:27:52,000 --> 00:27:54,640
Ah! Amelia Pond.

489
00:27:54,720 --> 00:27:58,360
Fish...fingers...and custard!

490
00:27:59,280 --> 00:28:02,000
Fish...fingers...

491
00:28:03,080 --> 00:28:06,960
and custard!

492
00:28:10,160 --> 00:28:12,240
-Mmm...
-It's good.

493
00:28:12,640 --> 00:28:15,160
(CLASSICAL MUSIC PLAYING)

494
00:28:20,320 --> 00:28:22,600
(ALL CHATTERING, INDISTINCT)

495
00:28:24,240 --> 00:28:25,400
(GUNSHOTS)

496
00:28:25,480 --> 00:28:27,400
(WOMEN SCREAMING)

497
00:28:30,760 --> 00:28:32,840
Ladies and gentlemen,

498
00:28:34,160 --> 00:28:36,360
I don't have a thing to wear.

499
00:28:36,560 --> 00:28:37,720
(CHUCKLES)

500
00:28:38,360 --> 00:28:40,320
Take off your clothes.

501
00:28:43,360 --> 00:28:46,040
Okay. All of Berlin, how do we find her?

502
00:28:46,120 --> 00:28:48,120
I don't know. Look for clues.

503
00:28:48,200 --> 00:28:50,440
-Clues? What kind of clues?
-Shut up!

504
00:28:50,520 --> 00:28:52,600
(SCREAMING)

505
00:28:55,200 --> 00:28:56,440
Okay...

506
00:29:00,240 --> 00:29:01,280
No...

507
00:29:07,120 --> 00:29:10,280
Hmm... Now look at that.

508
00:29:10,360 --> 00:29:11,720
Now, that's fun!

509
00:29:11,840 --> 00:29:14,840
(GIGGLING) From every angle.

510
00:29:19,600 --> 00:29:22,520
Now, dear, I told you not to follow me.

511
00:29:26,880 --> 00:29:28,040
(GASPING)

512
00:29:29,560 --> 00:29:32,080
Okay. Okay.

513
00:29:32,160 --> 00:29:35,480
I'm trapped inside
a giant robot replica of my wife.

514
00:29:36,120 --> 00:29:38,440
I'm really trying not to see this
as a metaphor.

515
00:29:38,520 --> 00:29:41,600
AMY: How can we be in here?
How do we fit?

516
00:29:42,080 --> 00:29:44,920
-Miniaturisation ray.
-How would you know that?

517
00:29:45,000 --> 00:29:48,040
Well, there was a ray
and we were miniaturised.

518
00:29:48,120 --> 00:29:49,400
(DOOR OPENING)

519
00:29:51,760 --> 00:29:54,160
Welcome, you are unauthorised.

520
00:29:54,320 --> 00:29:56,680
Your death will now be implemented.

521
00:29:56,760 --> 00:29:57,920
Um, what's that?

522
00:29:58,000 --> 00:29:59,800
Uh, I don't know. It's in your head!

523
00:29:59,880 --> 00:30:02,840
Please remain calm
while your life is terminated.

524
00:30:02,920 --> 00:30:04,800
-We come in peace!
-Ha ha. When has that ever worked?

525
00:30:04,880 --> 00:30:06,120
Oh, shut up!

526
00:30:06,200 --> 00:30:09,360
Please cooperate in your officially
sanctioned termination.

527
00:30:09,480 --> 00:30:12,200
It is normal to experience fear
during your incineration.

528
00:30:12,280 --> 00:30:13,880
-Stop, I got a sonic.
-What are you doing?

529
00:30:13,960 --> 00:30:15,680
-I don't know.
-Okay, psychic intervention.

530
00:30:15,760 --> 00:30:17,080
-Just point and think.
-What do I think?

531
00:30:17,160 --> 00:30:18,720
I don't know!

532
00:30:20,840 --> 00:30:23,600
It's okay. Stay still and don't move.

533
00:30:25,160 --> 00:30:26,880
Privileges activated.

534
00:30:26,960 --> 00:30:28,400
See? Activated.

535
00:30:28,480 --> 00:30:31,880
You are authorised.
Your existence will continue.

536
00:30:31,960 --> 00:30:34,120
You can put your hands down.

537
00:30:35,440 --> 00:30:37,920
This is Justice Department
Vehicle 6018.

538
00:30:38,000 --> 00:30:39,880
You're not guilty of anything.

539
00:30:40,920 --> 00:30:42,840
Welcome aboard the Tesselecta.

540
00:30:42,920 --> 00:30:45,400
I might take the age down a little.

541
00:30:46,040 --> 00:30:47,520
Just gradually,

542
00:30:47,960 --> 00:30:49,720
to freak people out.

543
00:30:50,280 --> 00:30:51,440
You killed the Doctor.

544
00:30:51,520 --> 00:30:53,160
Oh, yes, I know, dear.

545
00:30:53,240 --> 00:30:54,720
I hope you're not going to keep on
about it.

546
00:30:55,800 --> 00:30:57,760
Oh! Regeneration.

547
00:30:58,040 --> 00:31:00,800
It's a whole new colouring to work with.

548
00:31:00,880 --> 00:31:03,240
(CHUCKLING)

549
00:31:03,320 --> 00:31:04,680
You killed the Doctor.

550
00:31:04,760 --> 00:31:08,760
On the orders of the movement known as
the Silence and Academy of the Question.

551
00:31:08,840 --> 00:31:10,440
You accept and know this to be true.

552
00:31:10,520 --> 00:31:13,400
Quite honestly, I don't really remember.
It was all a bit of a jumble.

553
00:31:15,600 --> 00:31:19,080
No, no! Get off me!

554
00:31:19,440 --> 00:31:22,400
Sorry?
Did you say she killed the Doctor?

555
00:31:23,240 --> 00:31:24,480
The Doctor?

556
00:31:30,200 --> 00:31:31,600
Doctor who?

557
00:31:31,680 --> 00:31:33,480
-You said he was dying!
-WOMAN: He is.

558
00:31:33,560 --> 00:31:35,440
When you're done here,
your memories will be wiped

559
00:31:35,520 --> 00:31:37,680
-and you'll be able to...
-Doctor?

560
00:31:37,760 --> 00:31:39,120
RIVER: You're dying.

561
00:31:39,920 --> 00:31:41,760
And you stopped to change?

562
00:31:42,320 --> 00:31:45,400
Oh, you should always waste time
when you don't have any.

563
00:31:45,480 --> 00:31:48,680
Time is not the boss of you! Rule 408.

564
00:31:48,760 --> 00:31:51,400
Amelia Pond, judgement death machine.

565
00:31:51,560 --> 00:31:54,000
Why am I not surprised?

566
00:31:54,160 --> 00:31:55,600
Sonic cane.

567
00:31:55,680 --> 00:31:57,000
Are you serious?

568
00:31:57,080 --> 00:31:59,920
DOCTOR: Never knowingly.
Never knowingly be serious.

569
00:32:00,680 --> 00:32:02,880
Rule 27. You might want to
write these down.

570
00:32:03,840 --> 00:32:05,680
Oh! It's a robot!

571
00:32:07,000 --> 00:32:09,560
With 423 life signs inside,

572
00:32:09,640 --> 00:32:13,320
a robot worked by tiny people.

573
00:32:13,600 --> 00:32:15,560
Love it! But how did you all
get in there, though?

574
00:32:15,640 --> 00:32:17,760
Bigger on the inside?

575
00:32:18,040 --> 00:32:22,360
No. Basic miniaturisation
sustained by a compression field.

576
00:32:22,440 --> 00:32:25,600
Ooh! Watch what you eat.
It'll get you every time.

577
00:32:26,040 --> 00:32:28,960
Amy, if you and Rory are okay,
signal me.

578
00:32:31,640 --> 00:32:32,800
(BUZZING)

579
00:32:33,480 --> 00:32:34,560
Thanking you.

580
00:32:34,640 --> 00:32:35,760
MAN: How did you do that?

581
00:32:35,840 --> 00:32:38,760
(SCREAMING IN PAIN)

582
00:32:38,840 --> 00:32:40,960
So sorry. Leg went to sleep.

583
00:32:41,320 --> 00:32:44,880
Just had a quick left-leg power nap.
I forgot I had one scheduled.

584
00:32:44,960 --> 00:32:48,800
Actually, better sit down.
I think I heard the right one yawning.

585
00:32:50,440 --> 00:32:51,760
(SCREAMING)

586
00:32:52,200 --> 00:32:54,720
Don't you touch her!
Do not harm her in any way!

587
00:32:55,760 --> 00:32:57,200
(MOANING)

588
00:32:58,680 --> 00:33:01,520
Why would you care?
She's the woman who kills you.

589
00:33:03,320 --> 00:33:04,680
I'm not dead.

590
00:33:05,560 --> 00:33:06,920
You're dying.

591
00:33:07,080 --> 00:33:10,520
Well, at least I'm not
a time travelling, shape-shifting robot

592
00:33:10,600 --> 00:33:12,640
operated by miniaturised cross people,

593
00:33:12,720 --> 00:33:16,360
which I have got to admit
I didn't see coming.

594
00:33:17,320 --> 00:33:18,920
What do you want with her?

595
00:33:19,600 --> 00:33:20,680
She's Melody Pond.

596
00:33:21,080 --> 00:33:23,840
According to our records,
the woman who kills the Doctor.

597
00:33:24,320 --> 00:33:26,880
And I'm the Doctor,
so what's it got to do with you?

598
00:33:29,360 --> 00:33:30,400
(BEEPING)

599
00:33:31,920 --> 00:33:35,680
Throughout history, many criminals
have gone unpunished in their lifetimes.

600
00:33:35,760 --> 00:33:38,840
Time travel has...responsibilities.

601
00:33:39,200 --> 00:33:40,600
(LAUGHING)

602
00:33:41,840 --> 00:33:44,840
What? You got yourselves time travel

603
00:33:44,920 --> 00:33:47,600
so you decided to punish dead people?

604
00:33:48,160 --> 00:33:50,520
We don't kill them. We extract them

605
00:33:50,600 --> 00:33:52,760
near the end of their
established time lines.

606
00:33:53,360 --> 00:33:54,760
Then what?

607
00:33:56,560 --> 00:33:57,840
Give them hell.

608
00:34:02,880 --> 00:34:07,400
I'd ask you who you think you are, but
I think the answer is pretty obvious.

609
00:34:07,560 --> 00:34:09,680
So who do you think I am?

610
00:34:10,400 --> 00:34:11,520
Huh?

611
00:34:11,600 --> 00:34:15,200
The woman who killed the Doctor.

612
00:34:16,520 --> 00:34:18,560
It sounds like you've
got my biography in there.

613
00:34:18,640 --> 00:34:20,280
I'd love a peek.

614
00:34:21,600 --> 00:34:23,920
Our records office is sealed
to the public.

615
00:34:24,000 --> 00:34:25,360
Foreknowledge is dangerous.

616
00:34:25,440 --> 00:34:26,720
Yeah, well, I'll be dead
in three minutes.

617
00:34:26,800 --> 00:34:28,560
There isn't much foreknowledge left.

618
00:34:28,840 --> 00:34:30,520
Sorry, can't do that.

619
00:34:31,520 --> 00:34:32,840
That man is my best friend.

620
00:34:33,360 --> 00:34:34,880
That woman is my daughter.

621
00:34:35,240 --> 00:34:37,200
You give him anything he wants.

622
00:34:38,480 --> 00:34:39,960
If she's family, she has privileges.

623
00:34:47,640 --> 00:34:50,360
Say, "Access personal records,
the Doctor."”

624
00:34:50,680 --> 00:34:53,720
Access personal records, the Doctor.

625
00:34:53,800 --> 00:34:54,800
Records available.

626
00:34:56,480 --> 00:34:57,480
(GRUNTS)

627
00:34:58,920 --> 00:35:00,240
Question.

628
00:35:01,880 --> 00:35:03,160
I'm dying.

629
00:35:03,240 --> 00:35:05,240
-Who wants me dead?
-The Silence.

630
00:35:05,320 --> 00:35:07,960
What is the Silence?
Why is it called that? What...

631
00:35:08,120 --> 00:35:09,280
What does it mean?

632
00:35:09,360 --> 00:35:11,360
The Silence is not a species.

633
00:35:11,440 --> 00:35:13,600
It is a religious order or movement.

634
00:35:13,680 --> 00:35:16,920
Their core belief is that silence
will fall when the question is asked.

635
00:35:17,000 --> 00:35:18,200
What question?

636
00:35:18,280 --> 00:35:21,800
The first question.
The oldest question in the universe.

637
00:35:22,120 --> 00:35:23,440
Hidden in plain sight.

638
00:35:23,520 --> 00:35:25,560
Yes, but what is the question?

639
00:35:28,800 --> 00:35:30,040
Unknown.

640
00:35:31,120 --> 00:35:33,160
Oh, well, fat load of use that is,
you big ginge!

641
00:35:33,240 --> 00:35:34,440
You call yourselves the records...

642
00:35:34,520 --> 00:35:36,360
(SCREAMING)

643
00:35:38,480 --> 00:35:41,480
Kidneys are always the first to quit.

644
00:35:41,560 --> 00:35:43,560
Ahh... I've had better, you know.

645
00:35:43,960 --> 00:35:45,600
Okay, he's finished.

646
00:35:46,320 --> 00:35:47,680
Oh, my God!

647
00:35:48,240 --> 00:35:50,280
Well, then, let's do what we do.

648
00:35:51,200 --> 00:35:52,200
Give her hell!

649
00:35:53,000 --> 00:35:55,960
(SCREAMING)

650
00:35:57,200 --> 00:35:59,360
Amy, Rory...

651
00:35:59,640 --> 00:36:00,760
Amy...

652
00:36:01,280 --> 00:36:02,600
Can you hear me?

653
00:36:03,480 --> 00:36:04,560
Yeah.

654
00:36:06,000 --> 00:36:07,000
(BEEPING)

655
00:36:08,880 --> 00:36:09,920
You can talk to him.

656
00:36:12,000 --> 00:36:13,080
What do we do?

657
00:36:13,320 --> 00:36:15,720
This is me. This is me actually talking.
What do we do?

658
00:36:15,800 --> 00:36:18,320
Just stop them. She's your daughter.

659
00:36:18,840 --> 00:36:20,000
Just stop them!

660
00:36:20,280 --> 00:36:21,800
How, how? How?

661
00:36:21,880 --> 00:36:23,120
Just do it!

662
00:36:24,320 --> 00:36:26,480
Privileges activated. See?

663
00:36:26,560 --> 00:36:29,400
She is your daughter. Just stop them.

664
00:36:35,360 --> 00:36:36,480
RORY: What are you doing?

665
00:36:36,560 --> 00:36:38,360
Hunting and thinking. Get ready to run.

666
00:36:41,040 --> 00:36:42,440
(ALARM RINGING)

667
00:36:43,040 --> 00:36:46,720
You are unauthorised.
Your death will now be implemented.

668
00:36:46,960 --> 00:36:50,560
Okay, Captain, release her now
or I take down the whole Tesselecta.

669
00:36:50,640 --> 00:36:52,600
-Amy...
-You can't.

670
00:36:54,360 --> 00:36:55,560
Hey.

671
00:36:58,240 --> 00:36:59,800
(ALARMS BLARING)

672
00:37:02,400 --> 00:37:03,560
Rory, go!

673
00:37:04,760 --> 00:37:06,400
-All privileges withdrawn.
-What have you done?

674
00:37:06,480 --> 00:37:09,240
All life forms prepare
for immediate decease.

675
00:37:09,640 --> 00:37:12,600
You will experience a tingling sensation
and then death.

676
00:37:15,040 --> 00:37:16,840
-Shut it down!
-I'm trying!

677
00:37:16,920 --> 00:37:18,720
Shut everything down!

678
00:37:22,120 --> 00:37:23,160
Ahh!

679
00:37:25,040 --> 00:37:28,160
Please. Now we have to
save your parents.

680
00:37:28,720 --> 00:37:31,120
Don't run. Now, I know you're scared.

681
00:37:31,640 --> 00:37:33,280
But never run when you're scared.

682
00:37:33,360 --> 00:37:35,440
Rule seven. Please.

683
00:37:35,720 --> 00:37:38,160
Remain calm
while your life is extracted.

684
00:37:38,240 --> 00:37:39,720
-Come on, keep running!
-Where?

685
00:37:40,000 --> 00:37:41,800
I don't know. Just run!

686
00:37:41,920 --> 00:37:44,880
Mothership.
Mothership, get us out of here.

687
00:37:45,760 --> 00:37:47,160
Emergency beam-up now.

688
00:37:47,240 --> 00:37:48,360
Everyone!

689
00:37:53,800 --> 00:37:55,800
Only two life forms remain.

690
00:37:55,880 --> 00:37:57,720
This will be rectified.

691
00:38:01,440 --> 00:38:04,160
-Where'd everyone go?
-How can they just disappear?

692
00:38:06,040 --> 00:38:07,240
Doctor, can you hear us?

693
00:38:07,320 --> 00:38:08,560
Doctor?

694
00:38:09,200 --> 00:38:10,480
Doctor, help us!

695
00:38:10,560 --> 00:38:11,720
Doctor, help us!

696
00:38:13,720 --> 00:38:15,200
Doctor, please!

697
00:38:26,480 --> 00:38:27,680
(MOANING)

698
00:38:36,400 --> 00:38:38,040
AMY: Doctor...

699
00:38:38,120 --> 00:38:39,240
Help!

700
00:38:39,320 --> 00:38:40,720
RIVER: Look at you,

701
00:38:41,920 --> 00:38:43,320
you still care.

702
00:38:43,400 --> 00:38:44,840
Doctor, help!

703
00:38:45,520 --> 00:38:46,960
Doctor, help us!

704
00:38:47,040 --> 00:38:48,600
Please help us!

705
00:38:49,200 --> 00:38:51,080
It's impressive, I'll give you that.

706
00:38:51,880 --> 00:38:53,880
River, please.

707
00:38:54,160 --> 00:38:55,320
Again!

708
00:38:57,800 --> 00:38:59,320
Who is this River?

709
00:38:59,960 --> 00:39:01,520
She's got to be a woman.

710
00:39:02,280 --> 00:39:03,400
Am I right?

711
00:39:03,480 --> 00:39:05,040
DOCTOR: Help me...

712
00:39:05,320 --> 00:39:07,000
save Amy and Rory.

713
00:39:07,520 --> 00:39:08,600
Help me.

714
00:39:10,000 --> 00:39:11,480
Tell me about her.

715
00:39:13,640 --> 00:39:14,960
Go on.

716
00:39:15,040 --> 00:39:16,440
Ahh! Just...

717
00:39:21,120 --> 00:39:22,400
help me.

718
00:39:34,480 --> 00:39:36,240
(ECHOING) You are unauthorised.

719
00:39:36,320 --> 00:39:38,320
Your death will now be implemented.

720
00:39:38,400 --> 00:39:39,800
You are unauthorised.

721
00:39:39,880 --> 00:39:42,240
Your death will now be implemented.

722
00:39:42,360 --> 00:39:44,160
You are unauthorised.

723
00:39:45,640 --> 00:39:46,680
I love you.

724
00:39:47,720 --> 00:39:49,200
I love you, too.

725
00:39:51,160 --> 00:39:52,160
You are unauthorised.

726
00:39:52,240 --> 00:39:54,160
Your death will now be implemented.

727
00:39:55,400 --> 00:39:56,960
You are unauthorised.

728
00:39:57,040 --> 00:39:58,960
Your death will now be implemented.

729
00:39:59,400 --> 00:40:00,600
Doctor?

730
00:40:01,680 --> 00:40:02,800
Doctor, you did it!

731
00:40:02,880 --> 00:40:05,240
(BOTH LAUGHING) You did it!

732
00:40:05,320 --> 00:40:06,480
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

733
00:40:12,640 --> 00:40:14,480
I seem to be able to fly her.

734
00:40:15,680 --> 00:40:17,360
She showed me how.

735
00:40:18,560 --> 00:40:20,040
She taught me.

736
00:40:22,440 --> 00:40:25,920
The Doctor says I am the child
of the Tardis.

737
00:40:27,760 --> 00:40:29,440
What does he mean?

738
00:40:30,760 --> 00:40:32,160
Where is he?

739
00:40:37,360 --> 00:40:38,400
You can't die now.

740
00:40:39,280 --> 00:40:40,840
I know you don't die now.

741
00:40:41,400 --> 00:40:43,400
Oh, Pond!

742
00:40:43,880 --> 00:40:45,560
You've got a schedule for everything.

743
00:40:46,840 --> 00:40:49,280
It doesn't... It doesn't make any sense.

744
00:40:49,640 --> 00:40:51,920
Doctor, what do we do? Come on!

745
00:40:52,880 --> 00:40:54,400
How do we help you?

746
00:40:55,040 --> 00:40:56,600
Sorry, Rory, you can't.

747
00:40:57,680 --> 00:40:59,040
Nobody can.

748
00:41:00,360 --> 00:41:02,440
Ponds, listen to me.

749
00:41:04,160 --> 00:41:06,400
I need to talk to your daughter.

750
00:41:24,800 --> 00:41:26,080
Find her.

751
00:41:27,880 --> 00:41:29,440
Find River Song.

752
00:41:30,560 --> 00:41:32,600
And tell her something from me.

753
00:41:33,880 --> 00:41:35,320
Tell her what?

754
00:41:39,120 --> 00:41:40,880
(WHISPERING)

755
00:41:43,120 --> 00:41:45,800
(GASPING) Well, I'm sure she knows.

756
00:42:11,560 --> 00:42:13,160
Who's River Song?

757
00:42:24,720 --> 00:42:28,040
Are you still working?
Because I'm still a relative.

758
00:42:28,880 --> 00:42:30,960
Access files on River Song.

759
00:42:31,640 --> 00:42:33,240
Records available.

760
00:42:33,320 --> 00:42:34,720
Show me her.

761
00:42:35,320 --> 00:42:37,040
Show me River Song.

762
00:43:04,080 --> 00:43:05,120
Melody...

763
00:43:07,120 --> 00:43:08,720
What did he say?

764
00:43:08,920 --> 00:43:11,880
The Doctor gave you
a message for River Song.

765
00:43:12,240 --> 00:43:13,640
What was it?

766
00:43:19,880 --> 00:43:21,520
What's happening?

767
00:43:21,920 --> 00:43:23,960
River, what are you doing?

768
00:43:26,000 --> 00:43:27,520
Just tell me.

769
00:43:28,680 --> 00:43:29,840
The Doctor...

770
00:43:31,640 --> 00:43:33,120
Is he worth it?

771
00:43:34,160 --> 00:43:37,320
Yes! Yes, mmm-hmm, he is.

772
00:43:51,440 --> 00:43:52,800
(GASPING)

773
00:43:54,080 --> 00:43:55,280
River?

774
00:43:56,200 --> 00:43:58,800
No... What are you doing?

775
00:44:00,040 --> 00:44:01,920
Hello, sweetie.

776
00:44:31,760 --> 00:44:32,960
Hey.

777
00:44:34,000 --> 00:44:35,080
Hey.

778
00:44:38,680 --> 00:44:41,160
-Where am I?
-You're safe now.

779
00:44:42,080 --> 00:44:46,040
Apparently, you used all your remaining
regenerations in one go.

780
00:44:46,640 --> 00:44:48,080
You shouldn't have done that.

781
00:44:49,200 --> 00:44:50,400
Mother,

782
00:44:50,920 --> 00:44:52,400
I had to try.

783
00:44:53,200 --> 00:44:54,400
I know.

784
00:44:55,000 --> 00:44:57,240
He said no one could save him.

785
00:44:58,280 --> 00:45:00,480
But he must have known I could.

786
00:45:01,480 --> 00:45:02,480
Rule one,

787
00:45:04,920 --> 00:45:06,520
the Doctor lies.

788
00:45:10,560 --> 00:45:12,080
She just needs to rest.

789
00:45:12,160 --> 00:45:14,040
She'll be absolutely fine.

790
00:45:14,120 --> 00:45:15,240
No...

791
00:45:15,920 --> 00:45:17,040
she won't.

792
00:45:19,160 --> 00:45:20,640
She will be...

793
00:45:21,840 --> 00:45:23,120
amazing!

794
00:45:36,560 --> 00:45:38,480
So that's it? We just leave her there?

795
00:45:38,560 --> 00:45:40,640
Sisters of the Infinite Schism,

796
00:45:40,720 --> 00:45:42,280
greatest hospital in the universe.

797
00:45:42,360 --> 00:45:43,680
Yeah, but she's our daughter.

798
00:45:43,800 --> 00:45:45,520
Doctor, she's River,

799
00:45:45,640 --> 00:45:47,040
and she's our daughter.

800
00:45:47,160 --> 00:45:48,600
Amy, I know.

801
00:45:49,080 --> 00:45:51,760
But we have to let her
make her own way now.

802
00:45:51,840 --> 00:45:54,080
We have too much foreknowledge,
it's a...

803
00:45:56,400 --> 00:45:58,520
dangerous thing, foreknowledge.

804
00:45:59,440 --> 00:46:00,880
-What's that?
-Nothing!

805
00:46:00,960 --> 00:46:04,320
Just some data I downloaded from
the Tesselecta, very boring.

806
00:46:04,680 --> 00:46:06,440
Doctor, River was brainwashed
to kill you, right?

807
00:46:06,520 --> 00:46:09,960
Well, she did kill me and then she used
her remaining lives to bring me back.

808
00:46:10,040 --> 00:46:11,840
As firsts dates go,

809
00:46:11,920 --> 00:46:14,200
I'd say that was mixed signals.

810
00:46:14,280 --> 00:46:16,640
But that stuff
that they put in her head.

811
00:46:17,400 --> 00:46:19,000
Is that gone now?

812
00:46:19,280 --> 00:46:21,520
The River that we know in the future,

813
00:46:21,680 --> 00:46:24,400
she is in prison, for murder.

814
00:46:25,560 --> 00:46:27,040
Whose murder?

815
00:46:36,760 --> 00:46:38,000
Will we see her again?

816
00:46:38,080 --> 00:46:39,600
Oh, she'll come looking for us.

817
00:46:39,680 --> 00:46:42,680
Yeah, but how? How do people
even look for you?

818
00:46:43,040 --> 00:46:44,360
Oh, Pond!

819
00:46:45,320 --> 00:46:47,960
Haven't you figured that one out yet?

820
00:46:54,160 --> 00:46:55,920
So then, tell me,

821
00:46:58,000 --> 00:47:00,600
why do you want to study archaeology?

822
00:47:02,200 --> 00:47:04,880
Well, to be perfectly honest, Professor,

823
00:47:05,480 --> 00:47:07,560
I'm looking for a good man.

824
00:47:11,600 --> 00:47:14,560
(WHISPERING) Please save me
from the monsters.

825
00:47:15,640 --> 00:47:16,960
DOCTOR: Tell me about George.

826
00:47:17,040 --> 00:47:18,480
Well, he's scared to death
of everything.

827
00:47:18,560 --> 00:47:21,480
George, you have to face your fears.
You have to face them now!

828
00:47:21,560 --> 00:47:23,280
(SCREAMING)

829
00:47:24,520 --> 00:47:25,920
We're dead, again.

830
00:47:26,480 --> 00:47:28,720
You see these eyes? They're old eyes.

831
00:47:28,840 --> 00:47:29,960
(SCREAMING)

832
00:47:30,040 --> 00:47:32,320
The only thing I can tell you...

833
00:47:32,720 --> 00:47:34,000
monsters are real.

834
00:47:34,080 --> 00:47:35,120
(LAUGHING)

